<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-29T04:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-29T04:25:00-05:00" n="750" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">384.11/9: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-29T12:00:00+02:35">June 29, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:05
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>49. Department’s June 26, 2 p.m. American missionaries in capital
                                    who would follow advice to depart are prepared to depart
                                    immediately. A certain number may be expected to insist on
                                    remaining out of sense of duty. Potential danger varies
                                    according to locality outside capital and I have recommended
                                    immediate evacuation some stations. British Minister conferring
                                    with Emperor, and I shall telegraph further next week. News
                                    received unofficially that Eden visit to Rome complete failure.
                                    Impossible to estimate when hostilities may begin but Italian
                                    Legation urging remaining Italians to hasten departure. British
                                    Minister has plans for Legation evacuation but I intend to
                                    remain unless <pb facs="0980" n="878" xml:id="pg_878"/>
                                    instructed to go. My despatch 17<note n="83" xml:id="d750fn83">Not printed.</note> recommended including two Jackson
                                    negroes in destitute group.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>